(1, 'tr', 'Veri aktarmasι', '<p><strong>What means DataPortability to yiid users?</strong>  </p> <p>yiid aims for the possibility of moving all forms of personal data from one community to another via DataPortability. Users can move their data, such as profile, address, photos and friends. In doing so, they define their privacy settings and decide which data they want to move. A person whose private social network is focused on salsa dancing can put the focus on finding potential business partners in the business community. Users can individually adapt their profile to any kind of community.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Why DataPortability?</strong></p> <p>Because it saves time and effort. Any member of more than one community has certainly wondered if it is necessary to fill in the same profile and search for the same friends over and over again. Oh no! And where can I find my picture of the salsa party? The one in the right format? And where is my picture in suit and cravat? </p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>yiid and DataPortability </strong> </p> <p>The communipedia search engine offers searching across a wide range of special interest communities. It leads directly to the results on the community websites. Can you imagine becoming a member in the community offering excellent search results? Now, you can do it - immediately and quickly.</p> <p>The yiid team analyses the best ways to integrate DataPortability into yiid . In the future, every internet and Web2.0 user can directly and specifically find and access the right places in the Web 2.0 world.</p>'),
